    <p class="lead">The Maps collection currently contains nearly 22,000 Canadian maps digitized from the 1:50,000 scale National Topographic Series (1905–2012), covering all provinces and territories.</p>
    <p>These maps show landforms and terrain, drainage, forest cover, administrative areas, populated areas, transportation routes and facilities, and other human‑made features. Both colour and grayscale maps are included.</p>
    <p>The maps were digitized by McGill University Library and are presented here thanks to a partnership between McGill University Library and CRKN. Portions are also available through Scholars GeoPortal and Borealis as georeferenced datasets.</p>
    <p><strong>Size:</strong> Approximately 22,000 maps</p>
    <p><strong>Selection criteria:</strong> Currently focuses on the 1:50,000 National Topographic Series. The collection is not 100% complete and will be filled in as missing maps become available; other series may be added later.</p>

    <hr class="my-4"/>
    <h2 class="section-title h4">Cartes</h2>
    <p class="lead">La collection de cartes contient actuellement près de 24 000 cartes canadiennes numérisées à partir de la Série nationale de référence cartographique à l’échelle 1:50 000 (1905–2012), couvrant l’ensemble des provinces et territoires.</p>
    <p>Elles décrivent en détail le relief, le drainage, la couverture forestière, les zones administratives, les zones peuplées, les voies de transport et d’autres éléments anthropiques. La collection comprend des cartes en couleurs et en niveaux de gris.</p>
